## Mocking e Stubbing

### Usar Fake Objects
```kotlin
// ✅ CORRETO: Fake objects simples
class FakeMemberRepository : MemberRepository {
    val members = mutableListOf<Member>()
    
    override suspend fun addMember(member: Member): Member {
        members.add(member)
        return member
    }
}

// ❌ ERRADO: Mock complexo desnecessário
@Mock
lateinit var mockRepository: MemberRepository

@Before
fun setup() {
    MockitoAnnotations.openMocks(this)
    whenever(mockRepository.addMember(any())).thenReturn(member)
}
```

## Performance de Testes

### Regras
- **SEMPRE** usar in-memory database para testes
- **SEMPRE** usar fake objects em vez de mocks complexos
- **SEMPRE** limpar estado entre testes
- **NUNCA** fazer network calls em testes unitários
- **SEMPRE** usar coroutines test dispatcher

### Exemplo
```kotlin
@get:Rule
val mainDispatcherRule = MainDispatcherRule()

@Before
fun setup() {
    Dispatchers.setMain(UnconfinedTestDispatcher())
}

@After
fun tearDown() {
    Dispatchers.resetMain()
}
```